01:20.206 --> 01:23.459
MAN: (IN ITALIAN ACCENT) Okay,
so you want a little off of the top, eh?

01:23.543 --> 01:25.712
Yes, sir, it's no problem.

01:25.878 --> 01:29.215
Ha! Well, we don't get
many people up in these parts,

01:29.299 --> 01:30.717
kind of slow, you know.

01:30.800 --> 01:33.928
But I will make you
look-a sharp, yes, sir.

01:34.053 --> 01:38.057
You are in good hands with Tanino,
because I'm the best, eh?

01:38.266 --> 01:40.602
I've been cutting hair all of my life.

01:40.810 --> 01:44.397
No matter how big or small,
I cut them all.

01:44.939 --> 01:46.649
<i>Mamma Mia!</i>

01:46.858 --> 01:50.653
It's Jujunga,
the aboriginal bounty hunter.

01:50.862 --> 01:55.158
His blowgun has captured
the most elusive prey.

01:55.325 --> 01:57.327
A tattooed terror!

01:58.911 --> 02:01.831
What is he doing this far north?

02:02.081 --> 02:03.833
Must be on some kind of hunt.

02:03.916 --> 02:05.752
Certainly ain't here for the night life.

02:05.835 --> 02:06.836
(CHUCKLES)

02:06.919 --> 02:08.379
So, as I was saying...

02:08.796 --> 02:09.797
Hey!

02:10.048 --> 02:16.596
It's "I" and "Am,"
the infamous twins, bounty hunter legends.

02:16.804 --> 02:22.560
Their techniques are so cunning,
their abilities so in tune,

02:22.644 --> 02:26.689
it's rumored that
they share the same mind.

02:27.023 --> 02:30.652
Hey, that reminds me,
back in the old days,

02:30.735 --> 02:34.322
how I used to hang around the barber shop
with all of the customers...

02:34.530 --> 02:37.408
some with nice, black,
thick hair, you know,

02:37.575 --> 02:38.910
like all of... oh!

02:39.243 --> 02:41.371
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

02:41.579 --> 02:43.915
It's the gentleman.

02:44.207 --> 02:47.126
He's a nice fellow but deadly.

02:47.210 --> 02:50.380
This bounty hunter dueled with many,

02:50.463 --> 02:52.924
but none could escape his skill.

02:53.216 --> 02:55.718
The knives are his weapon of choice.

02:55.802 --> 03:00.390
Look at him. So stylish, oh, so fancy.

03:00.556 --> 03:02.350
Great hair.

03:02.433 --> 03:04.060
Eh? What's this?

03:04.519 --> 03:07.980
Huh? I've never seen this one before.

03:08.272 --> 03:09.732
Curious.

03:14.070 --> 03:16.155
Hah! A strange fellow.

03:16.364 --> 03:17.907
I wonder...

03:20.910 --> 03:22.453
(GRIPPING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

03:27.333 --> 03:28.334
(GASP)

03:28.418 --> 03:30.378
Oh, my-

03:31.838 --> 03:34.257
You. You're... you're...

03:34.465 --> 03:39.846
Boris... biggest,
baddest bounty hunter of all.

03:40.054 --> 03:41.055
<i>Da!</i>

03:43.933 --> 03:45.601
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

03:47.854 --> 03:49.689
(RUSSIAN FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)

04:32.440 --> 04:34.442
(SINISTER INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

05:14.690 --> 05:16.275
What is up here?

05:16.484 --> 05:20.029
It seems there
is a problem you cannot deny.

05:21.531 --> 05:24.951
We are all here for the same samurai.

05:25.284 --> 05:26.619
Indeed we are,

05:26.702 --> 05:31.749
but I see no reason to discuss this
in the most frigid of temperatures.

05:32.083 --> 05:35.211
I suggest that
we confer on this delicate matter

05:35.294 --> 05:38.589
inside this nearby vacant structure.

05:38.673 --> 05:40.383
<i>Da!</i> It is cold.

05:40.716 --> 05:47.682
- Mmm-hmm.
- Hmm.

05:54.480 --> 05:57.483
It seems we have amassed
quite a committee.

05:58.693 --> 06:01.863
But only one of us can claim this bounty.

06:02.113 --> 06:04.282
It seems that the one who goes first

06:04.365 --> 06:07.034
will have the best chance
of collecting everything.

06:07.910 --> 06:08.911
Pa-tooey!

06:12.123 --> 06:15.126
I have come here before everyone.

06:15.418 --> 06:17.169
I will go first.

06:21.090 --> 06:24.969
He has no chance
against the power of Jujunga.

06:25.177 --> 06:27.305
As the Samurai approaches,

06:27.513 --> 06:30.892
I shall sit
by the roadside playing the flute.

06:31.225 --> 06:34.979
He will pause a moment
and listen to the beautiful sounds...

06:35.730 --> 06:37.315
(MYSTICAL INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

06:40.776 --> 06:43.779
Slowly being lulled into false security.

06:47.992 --> 06:52.079
At the moment he's at his most vulnerable,
my trap is sprung.

06:53.414 --> 06:54.415
(WHACK)

06:54.498 --> 06:56.792
My flute is really a blowgun

06:56.918 --> 07:00.504
with darts dipped
in the most lethal of poisons.

07:01.756 --> 07:04.258
This bounty will be mine.

07:04.383 --> 07:05.593
WARRIOR: You will fail.

07:07.511 --> 07:09.096
Your plan is flawed.

07:09.180 --> 07:11.557
How? It has never failed me before.

07:11.682 --> 07:13.517
It cannot be defeated.

07:13.684 --> 07:15.895
The samurai's senses are too acute.

07:15.978 --> 07:18.230
He will hear you take a breath
before you fire,

07:18.314 --> 07:20.566
and easily avoid your dart completely.

07:20.650 --> 07:22.401
You wouldn't stand a chance.

07:22.610 --> 07:25.613
GENTLEMAN: The gentleman
reluctantly must agree

07:25.696 --> 07:27.949
with our mysterious friend.

07:28.032 --> 07:30.284
You lack a certain style,

07:30.409 --> 07:35.873
a savoir faire that is required
for this particular bounty,

07:36.332 --> 07:38.459
whereas I, on the other hand,

07:38.542 --> 07:44.966
have all the wit and panache necessary
to take on such a worthy adversary...

07:48.552 --> 07:50.262
(WESTERN INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

07:51.263 --> 07:55.226
For I shall meet
my most studious of samurais

07:55.309 --> 07:59.063
out on the field of honor in a duel...

07:59.480 --> 08:02.733
a duel of epic proportions.

08:03.192 --> 08:06.320
It is true the Samurai has great skills.

08:06.404 --> 08:10.866
That, no one can deny,
but on this day, my friends,

08:11.117 --> 08:17.623
it is the gentleman who will prevail,
for my talents are far superior

08:18.040 --> 08:22.211
and my strategy
is as sound as I am elegant.

08:22.545 --> 08:28.300
Yes, I will take advantage
of his intense concentration

08:28.551 --> 08:30.344
and split his focus,

08:30.761 --> 08:35.349
forcing him to choose
between life and death...

08:37.893 --> 08:43.149
My cloak acting as shield and decoy
for the coup de grace.

08:43.691 --> 08:45.317
Now, I'm not one to brag,

08:45.401 --> 08:50.072
but I must say that my blades
fly faster than any bullet.

08:50.531 --> 08:52.950
He will not be able to escape them.

08:53.034 --> 08:57.288
(CHUCKLES) I assure you, indeed,
this bounty will be mine.

08:57.455 --> 08:59.707
WARRIOR: It is definitely the end for you.

09:00.708 --> 09:01.876
Pardon me?

09:02.084 --> 09:04.503
He is too disciplined
to fall for your tricks.

09:04.670 --> 09:07.131
Your decoy alone is not strong enough.

09:08.382 --> 09:11.427
A stylish plan it sounds, indeed,

09:11.677 --> 09:13.012
but he is right.

09:13.137 --> 09:15.890
An attack like that will not succeed.

09:17.558 --> 09:19.185
Listen to our plan

09:19.268 --> 09:20.811
and you will see

09:21.103 --> 09:22.104
It is "I"

09:22.188 --> 09:24.774
and "Am" who will claim this bounty.

09:28.027 --> 09:29.236
(ORIENTAL INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

09:29.320 --> 09:34.784
As the Samurai enters the town,
we will wait for the final showdown.

09:35.034 --> 09:37.286
Concealed we will be.

09:38.829 --> 09:41.874
Our surprise he will never see.

09:44.210 --> 09:46.378
"I" will attack from the rear...

09:48.881 --> 09:51.550
And "Am" from the sun will appear.

09:51.842 --> 09:55.262
A thousand bombs will fall from the sky.

09:55.554 --> 10:00.726
In his confusion,
the Samurai will surely die.

10:03.312 --> 10:06.065
(BOTH CACKLING)

10:06.190 --> 10:07.441
WARRIOR: You're on the right track.

10:07.525 --> 10:09.568
But the two of you can never defeat Jack.

10:09.819 --> 10:12.154
Jack is cunning and hard to restrain.

10:12.238 --> 10:14.782
By leaving him a sword,
he stays in the game.

10:14.865 --> 10:15.866
(EXPLOSION)

10:15.950 --> 10:16.951
BORIS: Bah!

10:17.034 --> 10:18.744
Enough with this kiddie talk.

10:18.953 --> 10:20.162
(SPITS)

10:20.663 --> 10:24.375
Boris is best. Bounty belongs to Boris.

10:27.253 --> 10:28.629
(RUSSIAN FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)

10:28.712 --> 10:30.047
Little man is coming.

10:30.214 --> 10:32.091
I do not wait.

10:32.466 --> 10:33.676
Bah!

10:35.010 --> 10:37.179
He will attack with sword.

10:37.263 --> 10:39.473
It breaks against my belly.

10:40.641 --> 10:42.685
Then I break him!

10:42.852 --> 10:46.522
Break him! Break him! Break him!

10:46.689 --> 10:49.150
That's how Boris gets the bounty!

10:49.316 --> 10:51.110
Any questions?

10:51.277 --> 10:53.112
WARRIOR: Have you always been this stupid?

10:53.320 --> 10:54.530
Yes!

10:54.697 --> 10:56.574
What? What? No, uh, uh...

10:57.533 --> 10:59.410
You've underestimated your opponent.

10:59.743 --> 11:01.662
You have no idea what you're up against.

11:04.081 --> 11:06.208
You will all run headlong into death.

11:07.626 --> 11:08.627
What?

11:13.424 --> 11:14.425
(GROWLING)

11:22.391 --> 11:24.852
Your skills are most impressive,

11:24.977 --> 11:28.856
and your talents
certainly seem to match your wisdom.

11:28.939 --> 11:34.111
If you would be so inclined, kind sir,
to reveal yourself to us.

11:34.486 --> 11:36.530
(MYSTERIOUS INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

11:40.409 --> 11:41.660
A woman?

11:47.833 --> 11:49.210
Oh, my!

11:52.588 --> 11:55.049
I am Princess Mira of the Andaluvians.

11:55.299 --> 11:56.967
Oh.

11:58.260 --> 12:00.846
I've heard of her. She's powerful.

12:01.013 --> 12:07.353
Is she the one who captured that guy
on that planet, uh...

12:07.436 --> 12:08.437
Yes.

12:08.520 --> 12:10.898
Oh, my. Well, she is good.

12:11.065 --> 12:13.734
I have more power and skill
than all of you.

12:13.943 --> 12:17.404
It seems her tongue
bites as hard as her stick.

12:17.738 --> 12:20.824
But even I cannot
defeat the Samurai on my own.

12:21.116 --> 12:22.117
What's that?

12:22.743 --> 12:25.913
The only way to defeat him
is to join forces and attack him together,

12:25.996 --> 12:26.997
all at once.

12:27.081 --> 12:30.376
A wise and powerful plan this would be...

12:30.668 --> 12:33.754
but who is the one to claim the bounty?

12:34.046 --> 12:35.047
I am!

12:35.297 --> 12:36.799
BORIS: No woman will!

12:36.882 --> 12:39.885
Silence! I must claim this bounty.

12:40.886 --> 12:42.137
But not for the money.

12:44.431 --> 12:45.432
For freedom.

12:46.016 --> 12:49.270
The freedom of my people and my kingdom.

12:51.313 --> 12:56.777
Aku has enslaved my nation for many years,
plundering our wealth and resources.

12:57.236 --> 12:58.946
I will collect this bounty.

12:59.029 --> 13:01.490
And for payment, I will ask
for my people to be freed

13:01.740 --> 13:03.284
and my kingdom restored.

13:03.867 --> 13:07.246
In return for your help,
I will pay you the sum of the bounty,

13:07.579 --> 13:09.206
plus tenfold!

13:09.540 --> 13:10.833
My, my!

13:11.250 --> 13:12.835
That is much money.

13:13.043 --> 13:15.921
Her land has priceless resources.

13:16.005 --> 13:17.006
Priceless?

13:17.214 --> 13:19.008
So it seems.

13:19.133 --> 13:23.095
